# Literate Programming Example

This fixture exercises the code extraction API with multiple languages,
file attributes, and edge cases.

## Rust Implementation

::code[lang=rust file=src/main.rs]
fn main() {
    println!("Hello from SurfDoc!");
}
::

Some explanation between code blocks.

::code[lang=rust file=src/lib.rs]
pub fn add(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    a + b
}
::

## TypeScript Frontend

::code[lang=ts file=src/app.ts]
export function greet(name: string): string {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}
::

## Python Script

::code[lang=python]
def main():
    print("Hello from Python")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
::

## Shell Setup

::code[lang=sh file=setup.sh]
#!/bin/bash
echo "Setting up environment"
cargo build --release
::

